{
  "stem": "26111.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And from there, they, they, they-- from the last stop, they tried to cross the border there, were caught by a patrol, which apparently mainly consisted of a young recruit, who was still, still very raw and still had his-- had some humanity left, and accepted a bribe and let them go.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then they tried again.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this time, they were caught for real by a real patrol, real soldiers, accompanied by real SS.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, and that was it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were at first, it seems, put into a concentration camp near Innsbruck and from there, sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I have had no-- and no one has had any news from them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the assumption, of course, is that they perished there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were killed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I didn't know for many years that it was Auschwitz because the information that I got, of course, was from the people that helped her-- helped them-- helped my parents escape.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They didn't know the details of what happened after they were caught, since only somebody close to the Nazis or close to the government would, would be able to find that out.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they weren't that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I found this out when I-- on a visit much later after the war, in '71, my first visit to Berlin after the war.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I, I went to the Office of Jewish Affairs, which had been set up and which collected documents and various other things-- information.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
